## Project

FitWell là ứng dụng phục hồi cơ xương khớp (MSK) dành cho nam giới văn phòng 35–50 tuổi tại Hà Nội và TP.HCM. Core loop: user mô tả triệu chứng → AI giao đúng protocol → daily check-in → progress tracking. Moat là longitudinal pattern data tích luỹ theo thời gian — switching cost tăng tự nhiên. MVP là web-first (Astro + React + Tailwind trên Vercel).

## Tech Stack

- Frontend: Astro + React + Tailwind CSS — deployed on Vercel
- Backend: Fastify + Node.js — deployed on DigitalOcean Singapore
- Database: PostgreSQL via Supabase (service_role key, RLS disabled by design)
- Auth: JWT in-memory only (no localStorage) + httpOnly refresh cookies
- AI: Claude Haiku (triage/check-in response) + Claude Sonnet (protocol assignment)
- Video: Cloudflare Stream
- Payments: PayOS (desktop QR polling + mobile redirect — two separate flows)
- Email: Resend
- Push: Web Push via VAPID + Service Worker

## Tier Scope — Active Sprint

**Tier 1 only.** Do not build Tier 2 or Tier 3 features.

Tier 1 screens:
- Symptom intake (3-question onboarding)
- Protocol assignment (AI response + first exercise)
- Daily check-in
- Progress tracking (pain score timeline)
- Exercise video player (Cloudflare Stream)

## Out of Scope — Do Not Build

- Pattern memory and proactive nudges — Tier 2
- Adaptive protocol switching — Tier 2
- Paywall and billing screens — Tier 3
- 7-day trial conversion flow — Tier 3
- Re-engagement flow after churn — Tier 3
- Condition expansion beyond initial 5 MSK entries — post-Tier 1
- Native iOS/Android app — post-MVP validation
- Social or community features — not in roadmap

## Build Rules

- Build Tier 1 screens only — reject any feature request that is Out of Scope above
- One component per file
- No inline styles — use Tailwind utility classes only, no arbitrary values like `p-[13px]`
- No hardcoded hex values — use design token class names from design-system
- All API calls must match endpoint contracts in FitWell_TechSpec
- Absolute imports from `@/` — never relative imports going up more than one level
- JWT must never be stored in localStorage or sessionStorage — in-memory only
- Refresh token must be set as httpOnly cookie by the server — never by client code
- All API error responses must be normalized — never expose raw database errors to client
- After every Supabase migration call, write the same SQL to `supabase/migrations/YYYYMMDDHHmmss_description.sql`

## LLM Usage

- Default to SQL and templates for all deterministic logic — no LLM for structured data retrieval
- LLM calls approved only for:
  - Symptom intake → protocol assignment (Claude Sonnet)
  - Daily check-in response generation (Claude Haiku)
  - Pain score interpretation (Claude Haiku)
- All other logic (scheduling, notification dispatch, progress calculation) must use SQL or templates
- Monthly inference cost ceiling: $60/month

## Auth Rules

- Anonymous sessions are supported — do not require login to start onboarding
- JWT access token: 15-minute TTL, stored in-memory only
- Refresh token: 7-day TTL, httpOnly cookie
- Never call Supabase with anon key for authenticated operations — use service_role key via backend only

## Payment Rules

- PayOS has two separate flows — never merge them:
  - Desktop: QR code generation + polling for payment confirmation
  - Mobile: redirect to PayOS payment URL, return via callback
- Never store credit card data — PayOS handles all PCI-sensitive data
- Payment confirmation must be verified server-side — never trust client-side payment status

## Copy Rules

- All UI copy in Vietnamese — no English copy visible to users
- Use "bạn" throughout — never "anh", "chị", or gendered pronouns
- No exclamation marks in any UI copy
- No emoji in any UI copy
- No motivational filler phrases ("Tuyệt vời!", "Bạn đang làm rất tốt!")
- Every copy slot must contain real data variables — never lorem ipsum or placeholder strings
- Sentences max 20 words
- Protocol format: `[Tên bài] · [Thời lượng] · [Địa điểm]`
